import pubchempy

n = 1000
n_page = 100

data = []
for i in range(n_page):
    print(i)
    data.extend(pubchempy.get_properties(properties = 'canonical_smiles',
                                         searchtype = 'substructure',
                                         identifier = 'N=[N+]=[N-]',
                                         namespace = 'smiles',
                                         listkey_count = n,
                                         listkey_start = i))

Для Lipinski rule of five в качестве пороговых значений возьмем значения из лекции

In [10]:
NUM_H_DONORS = 5
NUM_H_ACCEPTORS = 10
EXACT_MOL_WT = 500
CRIPPEN_DESCRIPTORS = 5

def is_lipinski(mol):
    return Lipinksy.NumHDonors(mol) <= NUM_H_DONORS \
        and Lipinksy.NumHAcceptors(mol) <= NUM_H_ACCEPTORS \
        and Lipinksy.rdMolDescriptors.CalcExactMolWt(mol) < EXACT_MOL_WT \
        and Lipinksy.rdMolDescriptors.CalcCrippenDescriptors(mol)[0] <= CRIPPEN_DESCRIPTORS
In [11]:
mols = []
smis = []

for smi in filtered_smiles:
    try:
        mol = Chem.MolFromSmiles(smi)
        if is_lipinski(mol):
            mols.append(mol)
            smis.append(smi)
    except Exception:
        # happens sometimes
        pass

mols = [mol for mol in mols if mol.HasSubstructMatch(modified_ibu)]
